> Basically, the way I read your post is this : your data isn't
> worth much and so Clipper suits your purposes just fine.

Of equal importance is the question "important to whom?".  Escrowed keys
create a two-tiered system where non-governmental eavesdroppers are forced
to either use brute force to crack the code, or else bribery or other
means to obtain the escrowed keys.  A governmental eavesdropper would have a
much easier time of it - finding a friendly judge to issue a court order.

